data.name: Egg and Spinach Toast
data.quickTastyDescription: A healthy and delicious open-faced sandwich featuring creamy scrambled eggs and vibrant spinach on toasted bread, perfect for breakfast or a light lunch.
detailedCookingInstructions: Toast the slices of whole grain bread until golden brown.
In a skillet, melt the butter over medium heat.
Add the fresh spinach and sauté until wilted, about 2-3 minutes.
In a bowl, whisk together the eggs, milk, salt, pepper, and garlic powder.
Pour the egg mixture into the skillet with the spinach, stirring gently until the eggs are just set and creamy.
Spoon the scrambled eggs and spinach mixture onto the toasted bread and serve immediately.
data.modifiersForBase: Creamy scrambled eggs and sautéed spinach
